<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
  <title>Cybersecurity Basics</title>
  <style>
    body {
      font-family: 'Segoe UI', Tahoma, Geneva, Verdana, sans-serif;
      margin: 0;
      padding: 0;
      background-color: #f4f4f4;
      color: #333;
    }

    header {
      background-color: #007BFF;
      color: #fff;
      padding: 20px;
      text-align: center;
    }

    h1 {
      margin: 0;
      font-size: 2em;
    }

    main {
      max-width: 800px;
      margin: 20px auto;
      background-color: #fff;
      box-shadow: 0 0 10px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1);
      padding: 20px;
      border-radius: 8px;
    }

    h2 {
      color: #007BFF;
    }

    p {
      line-height: 1.6;
    }

    .module {
      margin-bottom: 20px;
    }

    .quiz-container {
      margin-top: 20px;
    }

    form {
      margin-top: 15px;
    }

    label {
      display: block;
      margin-bottom: 8px;
    }

    input[type="radio"] {
      margin-bottom: 10px;
    }

    input[type="submit"] {
      background-color: #007BFF;
      color: #fff;
      padding: 10px 15px;
      border: none;
      border-radius: 4px;
      cursor: pointer;
    }

    input[type="submit"]:hover {
      background-color: #0056b3;
    }

    footer {
      background-color: #007BFF;
      color: #fff;
      text-align: center;
      padding: 10px 0;
      position: fixed;
      bottom: 0;
      width: 100%;
    }
  </style>
</head>
<body>

  <header>
    <h1>Cybersecurity Basics</h1>
  </header>

  <main>
    <div class="module">
      <h2>Module 1: Introduction to Cybersecurity</h2>
      <p>
        Welcome to the Introduction module. In this module, you'll learn the fundamentals of cybersecurity, including its importance and key concepts.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="module">
      <h2>Module 2: Password Security</h2>
      <p>
        In this module, we'll explore best practices for creating and managing secure passwords to protect your accounts from unauthorized access.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="module">
      <h2>Module 3: Malware Awareness</h2>
      <p>
        Malware poses a significant threat to cybersecurity. Learn about different types of malware and how to safeguard your systems against them.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="module">
      <h2>Module 4: Network Security</h2>
      <p>
        Network security is crucial for protecting data in transit. Discover essential concepts and practices for securing your network infrastructure.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="module">
      <h2>Module 5: Social Engineering</h2>
      <p>
        Social engineering attacks exploit human psychology. Understand common social engineering techniques and how to avoid falling victim to them.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="quiz-container">
      <h2>Quiz</h2>
      <form>
        <label for="q1">Question 1: What is the primary goal of cybersecurity?</label>
        <br>
        <input type="radio" name="q1" value="a"> Protecting personal privacy<br>
        <input type="radio" name="q1" value="b"> Preventing unauthorized access<br>
        <input type="radio" name="q1" value="c"> Ensuring fast internet speed<br>
        <br>

        <label for="q2">Question 2: What is a common method of social engineering?</label>
        <br>
        <input type="radio" name="q2" value="a"> Phishing<br>
        <input type="radio" name="q2" value="b"> Firewall setup<br>
        <input type="radio" name="q2" value="c"> Data encryption<br>
        <br>

        <!-- Add more questions as needed -->

        <input type="submit" value="Submit">
      </form>
    </div>
  </main>

  <footer>
    &copy; 2024 Cybersecurity Basics
  </footer>

</body>
</html>
